article.description: Trey Kennedy scored 18, including two free throws with 14 seconds left in overtime, and Southern Utah beat Idaho 85-83 Saturday night.
article.headline: Overtime run lifts Southern Utah over Idaho 85-83
article.linkText: Overtime run lifts Southern Utah over Idaho 85-83
article.story: MOSCOW, Idaho -- Trey Kennedy scored 18, including two free throws with 14 seconds left in overtime, and Southern Utah beat Idaho 85-83 Saturday night. Race Parsons scored 15 and James McGee hit four 3-pointers and finished with 14 points for Southern Utah (4-11, 2/3 Big Sky Conference), which snapped a three-game skid. Parsons hit a 3, sparking a 13-1 run that gave the Thunderbirds an 83-77 lead with 21 seconds left in overtime. Chris Sarbaugh converted a 3-point play to pull Idaho (11-7, 3-2) within three before Kennedy's free throws made it 85-80. Patrick Ingram made a layup with four seconds left and, after Southern Utah stepped on the baseline following the inbounds pass, Chad Sherwood was fouled on a 3-point attempt with 0.1 seconds left but missed 2 of 3 free throws. Victor Sanders, who scored a career-high 33 in a win over Northern Arizona on Thursday, scored 29 for Idaho.
